    <title>Protecting Domestic Violence and Stalking Victims Act of 2015</title>
    <summaries>
      <billSummaries>
        <item>
          <versionCode>00</versionCode>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><strong></strong><b>Protecting Domestic Violence and Stalking Victims Act of 2015</b></p> <p>This bill amends the federal criminal code to: </p> <ul> <li> state that the term &quot;intimate partner&quot; includes a dating partner and any other person subject to a protection order under state domestic or family violence law; and</li> <li> expand the term &quot;misdemeanor crime of domestic violence&quot; to include the use or attempted use of physical force, or the threatened use of a deadly weapon, by a current or former intimate partner. </li> </ul> <p>The bill makes it a crime to knowingly sell or dispose of a firearm to a person who has been convicted of a misdemeanor crime of stalking. It also makes it a crime for such convicted stalker to receive or possess a firearm. </p>]]></text>
          <updateDate>2015-06-04T04:00:00Z</updateDate>
